OK, so table flipping
isn't for everybody.

00:27:48.340 --> 00:27:51.270
But I think what's
important here

00:27:51.270 --> 00:27:54.780
is that games have a variety of
ways of helping people express

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:56.880
themselves, either in
very personal ways,

00:27:56.880 --> 00:27:59.980
or as it were, very inane ways.

00:27:59.980 --> 00:28:01.770
Play Games has a
number of tools that

00:28:01.770 --> 00:28:04.580
help you tap into that
sense of accomplishment,

00:28:04.580 --> 00:28:07.000
help people express
themselves to others.

00:28:07.000 --> 00:28:09.800
And we provide a platform
in which you can do it.

00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:12.560
The great thing about
achievements, for example,

00:28:12.560 --> 00:28:15.440
is they inform your players
of the depth of your game

00:28:15.440 --> 00:28:18.710
that otherwise you
wouldn't have discovered.

00:28:18.710 --> 00:28:22.530
When I finish playing a game
like "Hitman GO" and I've

00:28:22.530 --> 00:28:25.210
completed all the levels,
but these achievements

00:28:25.210 --> 00:28:25.920
give me hints.

00:28:25.920 --> 00:28:27.600
They're almost like a
guideline of what else

00:28:27.600 --> 00:28:28.480
I can do in the game.

00:28:28.480 --> 00:28:30.438
And they cause me to play
the game differently.

00:28:30.438 --> 00:28:32.580
They cause me to play
it longer in an effort

00:28:32.580 --> 00:28:34.830
to explore and complete
all the content.

00:28:34.830 --> 00:28:37.670
And in return, we've
seen game developers

00:28:37.670 --> 00:28:40.640
see pretty significant bumps
in day over day engagement

00:28:40.640 --> 00:28:42.380
through great
achievement design.

00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:45.510
And exposing that information
at a platform level

00:28:45.510 --> 00:28:48.220
is a way that we draw people
back in through the Play Games

00:28:48.220 --> 00:28:50.580
platform.

