00:30:47.452 --> 00:30:49.160
And players will never
have to play level

00:30:49.160 --> 00:30:51.280
one again in your game
across any screen.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:53.180
But what we can also
allow you to do now

00:30:53.180 --> 00:30:56.430
is give us a screen shot or
cover image and description

00:30:56.430 --> 00:30:57.750
and time played.

00:30:57.750 --> 00:31:01.330
And we expose those in the
Play Games experiences.

00:31:01.330 --> 00:31:04.277
And so if I go on
vacation, and I

00:31:04.277 --> 00:31:06.860
forgot that I'm playing a game
like "Leo's Fortune" at the top

00:31:06.860 --> 00:31:10.360
there, I'll pop open my app,
and I'll be like, oh yeah,

00:31:10.360 --> 00:31:11.290
that's right.

00:31:11.290 --> 00:31:12.690
I did leave off
at a level three.

00:31:12.690 --> 00:31:13.960
And I remember loving that game.

00:31:13.960 --> 00:31:15.668
And I'm going to
continue to play it now.

00:31:15.668 --> 00:31:18.161
So it really acts as
a digital bookmark,

00:31:18.161 --> 00:31:20.210
attracting players to
come back to your game.

00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:24.240
And we think it's a neat
little retention tool.

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:27.110
OK, and last, but
certainly not least,

00:31:27.110 --> 00:31:31.720
I'm going to talk about
building a sense of belonging.

00:31:31.720 --> 00:31:35.170
Perhaps the best story I can
tell here is through the game

00:31:35.170 --> 00:31:39.760
"High School Story,"
from Pixelberry Studios.

00:31:39.760 --> 00:31:41.760
They're here in the
Bay Area and decided

00:31:41.760 --> 00:31:43.770
that they'd take a strong
position on building

00:31:43.770 --> 00:31:46.870
a feeling of belonging
through game design.

00:31:46.870 --> 00:31:49.550
This game here, "High School
Story," started with the notion

00:31:49.550 --> 00:31:52.550
that growing up in high
school years is hard.

00:31:52.550 --> 00:31:55.226
And fitting in is a
general problem for all.

00:31:55.226 --> 00:31:56.600
And there's a very
powerful story

00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:59.395
by creating a sense of
belonging here and helping

00:31:59.395 --> 00:32:01.420
with the issue of cyberbullying.

00:32:01.420 --> 00:32:05.649
And this story is really best
told by their CEO, Oliver Miao.

00:32:05.649 --> 00:32:06.315
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:32:06.315 --> 00:32:10.430
-We designed "High School Story"
to be about a group of misfits

00:32:10.430 --> 00:32:12.570
who don't always fit in
at their old high school,

00:32:12.570 --> 00:32:15.520
and they've come together to
design their dream high school.

00:32:15.520 --> 00:32:17.070
Because of our
story line, we have

00:32:17.070 --> 00:32:20.960
a lot of players who've told
us that the game has given them

00:32:20.960 --> 00:32:22.730
more self confidence
or the ability

00:32:22.730 --> 00:32:25.520
to feel like they can
just be themselves.

00:32:25.520 --> 00:32:29.290
And so it's messages like that
that really have encouraged

00:32:29.290 --> 00:32:32.990
us to continue with these
type of story lines.

00:32:32.990 --> 00:32:36.200
But we were really
shocked when we

00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:39.990
had a message from a player
that was much more serious.

00:32:39.990 --> 00:32:43.120
We had a player reach out to
us via our in-game support.

00:32:43.120 --> 00:32:46.030
And she told us that she was
planning to kill herself.

00:32:46.030 --> 00:32:48.540
We were surprised,
shocked, and scared.

00:32:48.540 --> 00:32:50.780
We didn't know what to do.

00:32:50.780 --> 00:32:53.034
We called the suicide
prevention hotline.

00:32:53.034 --> 00:32:55.415
And based on their
advice, we urged

00:32:55.415 --> 00:32:56.930
her to get professional help.

00:32:56.930 --> 00:33:00.620
But we also let her know that
we were there to listen to her.

00:33:00.620 --> 00:33:03.910
And over time, after
exchange messages with her

00:33:03.910 --> 00:33:06.020
for about a week, she told
us that she was finally

00:33:06.020 --> 00:33:09.650
getting professional help and
that it was because of our game

00:33:09.650 --> 00:33:11.090
that she was still there.

00:33:11.090 --> 00:33:14.440
That incident showed us
the power of the game

00:33:14.440 --> 00:33:16.990
and how when players
feel connected to a game

00:33:16.990 --> 00:33:19.870
and to a community, it
can make a real difference

00:33:19.870 --> 00:33:20.975
in their lives.

00:33:20.975 --> 00:33:23.690
After that, we partnered with
the Cybersmile Foundation

00:33:23.690 --> 00:33:25.785
to create a special
cyberbullying story

00:33:25.785 --> 00:33:29.090
line that teachers players what
to do if they or their friends

00:33:29.090 --> 00:33:30.360
are being bullied.

00:33:30.360 --> 00:33:32.780
Players also are given
links to Cybersmile.

00:33:32.780 --> 00:33:36.980
And if they have questions,
directly from within the game,

00:33:36.980 --> 00:33:40.590
they're connected to
Cybersmile counselors.

00:33:40.590 --> 00:33:43.200
As a result, every week,
over 100 of our players

00:33:43.200 --> 00:33:45.110
get in touch with Cybersmile.

00:33:45.110 --> 00:33:48.270
These are players who are
often being bullied, sometimes

00:33:48.270 --> 00:33:52.060
self-hurting, or even
thinking about suicide.

00:33:52.060 --> 00:33:54.290
In fact, they shared
with us a story

00:33:54.290 --> 00:33:56.720
about a player who
was on a rooftop,

00:33:56.720 --> 00:33:59.140
and they were able to talk
the player down, get them

00:33:59.140 --> 00:34:02.460
in touch with their parents,
and help get their life back

00:34:02.460 --> 00:34:03.250
on track.

00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:05.950
Those type of stories
are amazing to us.

00:34:05.950 --> 00:34:07.830
We started our game
thinking that we

00:34:07.830 --> 00:34:12.632
have a great source of
entertainment for players,

00:34:12.632 --> 00:34:15.200
and if we could, we could
help build some community.

00:34:15.200 --> 00:34:20.239
But knowing that our game has
been involved in saving lives,

00:34:20.239 --> 00:34:22.300
helping people have
self confidence,

00:34:22.300 --> 00:34:24.325
and connecting them
to their parents

00:34:24.325 --> 00:34:28.849
and their friends has been
really inspiration to us.

00:34:28.849 --> 00:34:30.610
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:34:30.610 --> 00:34:32.130
So that's a deep topic.

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:34.870
Not every game can
claim that they tangibly

00:34:34.870 --> 00:34:39.830
help people to save
themselves from themselves.

00:34:39.830 --> 00:34:42.305
And what's really fantastic
about what Pixelberry Studios

00:34:42.305 --> 00:34:45.370
is doing is helping raise
awareness with their players

00:34:45.370 --> 00:34:48.219
and recognizing the
damage that cyberbullying

00:34:48.219 --> 00:34:50.080
has on people's lives.

00:34:50.080 --> 00:34:52.090
And for those
individuals, this game's

00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:53.520
been able to give
them that sense

00:34:53.520 --> 00:34:54.853
that there's somebody out there.

00:34:54.853 --> 00:34:57.820
It gives them that
feeling of belonging.

00:34:57.820 --> 00:35:01.250
It helped encourage them to
reach out in an environment

00:35:01.250 --> 00:35:04.520
where they may have
otherwise not chosen to.

00:35:04.520 --> 00:35:06.960
But this isn't just
merely because they

00:35:06.960 --> 00:35:09.130
decided to make a game
called "High School Story."

00:35:09.130 --> 00:35:10.980
It's really because
their design goals

00:35:10.980 --> 00:35:13.254
are the reason why they
became effective at this.

00:35:13.254 --> 00:35:14.670
And so when you
look at the things

00:35:14.670 --> 00:35:16.200
that they took into
account and talk

00:35:16.200 --> 00:35:18.100
to them about their
game design objectives,

00:35:18.100 --> 00:35:20.890
they take into account race
and gender and, of course,

00:35:20.890 --> 00:35:23.830
the anti-bullying message
that you heard earlier.

00:35:23.830 --> 00:35:25.545
So players identify
with characters

